The pregame news conference was held before the Heat tipped off against the Boston Celtics. 

During his seven-minute talk, Bosh detailed how he is feeling physically and talked about the emotional toll the ordeal has taken on him.

He said: 'I pretty much stay at home.

'Just recently, I started driving around the block.

'Of course, being around my children, my family and my wife and everything, I've just been really playing with my kids as much as I can.'

Bosh also thanked his well-wishers for their support and prayers. 

He added: 'I feel that all the love and energy has really allowed me to be back here, not under the circumstances I want to be, but beggars can't be choosers.'

