The All Star admitted the thought of retirement crossed his mind, then vanished.

He said: 'That subject did come up, but that was only a possibility.

'I'm very happy to be here and I'm doing a lot better. 

'I knew I was going to play basketball again.'

He also was featured in a segment that aired on Good Morning America. 

Bosh revealed the pain crept became too much for him while he was vacationing, during his interview with ABC News.

He said: 'Myself, my wife, Dwyane [Wade] and Gabrielle [Union] all went to Haiti. 

'I pretty much suffered for two days. 

'On, you know, the third day, we came back and I went right to the doctor's office.' 

